&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Locum Consultant Physician in Acute Medicine&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Advert&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking to appoint a new Locum Consultant Physician in Acute Medicine. The posts offer an exciting opportunity to join a friendly and forward looking consultant team and to develop new models of care/services that support the people of Tower Hamlets. It is an ideal first consultant post with strong clinical support and mentoring from experience senior colleagues! The posts have at their core an Acute Medical service with cover of the Acute Assessment Unit (AAU) and the medical take. Included in the job plan is also up to 3 PAs in a medical specialty. Should the appointee specialise in Acute Medicine, the specialty sessions will be undertaken within Acute Medicine/Ambulatory Care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This locum post is for six months.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You require full registration with the General Medical Council with the licence to practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information please contact Dr Dakshitha Hettiaratchi (Clinical Lead) Dakshitha.hettiaratchi1@nhs.net, telephone 020 7377 7000&lt;/p&gt;
